>>python -V
Python 3.6.8
>>pip -V
pip 20.1.1

Then try to install a package via pip (e.g. matplotlib, pandas,etc)
>>pip install matplotlib
Get SSL: CERTIFICATE_VERIFY_FALED, then ERROR: Could not find a version that satisfies the requirement matplotlib (from versions: none) ERROR: No matching distribution found for matplotlib

Permanent fix:
>>pip install matplotlib --trusted-host pypi.org --trusted-host files.pythonhosted.org

++ To verify which version of matplotlib:
>>python
>>import matplotlib
>>matplotlib.__version__
'3.3.0'
